bioghist.head: Historical Note
bioghist.p: The Urban and Regional Planning Department was created in 1968. It was discontinued as a department in the early 1990s.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Materials in this collection includes original construction drawings for Gelman library and 2000 Pennsylvania Avenue, student forms, handbook for preparing theses, syllabi, newsletters, departmental history, articles, community project files (Washington, D.C. and neighborhoods), and slides. This collection covers the years 1961-1993. Much of this material was transferred to University Archives by Professor Stephen S. Fuller. Note: Not all series are processed. Ask staff for assistance.

arrangement.head: Collection Organization
arrangement.p: Organized into four series: two series of Departmental files and one series each of Drawings and Slides.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: This collection is open for research.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: This series contains construction drawings. This material dates from 1971-80. These original construction drawings are for Gelman Library and 2000 Pennsylvania Avenue. This material is from the School of Business and Public Management, Urban Planning and Real Estate Development.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: This series contains student forms, handbook for preparing theses, syllabi, newsletters, departmental history, articles, community project files (Washington, D.C. area neighborhoods, etc.). The material dates from 1968-93. This material comes from the Urban Planning and Real Estate Development Government program.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: This series contains slides. The dates cover 1968-81. These more than 400 slides are images The George Washington University buildings, the University Yard, campus and the Foggy Bottom neighborhood, images of George Washington, models and plans of campus area land use. This material comes from the School of Business and Public Management, Urban and Regional Planning.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents note
scopecontent.p: This series includes correspondence, publications, studies, invitations, application, brochures, memorandums, articles, biographical information, proposals, reports, news releases, syllabuses, and a survey. They range in date from 1961 to 1990. They concern the seminars, conferences, teach evaluations, the Department of Urban and Regional Planing, accreditation for the masters of Urban and Regional Planning, a Center for Urban and Regional Studies, course requirements, Del Ray, Historic Preservation programs, and Mt. Pleasant neighborhood, and Dorn C. McGrath, Jr.
